==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[congratulari]]'', from ''[[gratus]]'', “pleasing”.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|congratulat|ing}}

# to [[express]] one’s [[sympathetic]] [[pleasure]] or [[joy]] to the person(s) it is [[felt]] for

